         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1/7/90 ¶  ¶ […]  ¶  ¶ It will much facilitate matters if you will communicate  ¶ direct ¶ [ly] with Baron Mueller where desirable. I thought you were already in correspondence with him as usual. Whate...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.07.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Joseph Maiden to Wilhelm Bäuerlen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MRS 15/1, Letterbook, Collector, 1890-1920, p. 34, Archives of the Powerhouse Museum, Sydney</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="Standard"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 6 November 1992. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>1/7/90<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">this is re 350/90.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…] </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will much facilitate matters if you will communicate <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">direct</hi>
               </seg>[ly] with Baron Mueller where desirable. I thought you were already in correspondence with him as usual. Whatever you do keep on good terms with him, for he has been very good in giving us information when we have desired it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please ask the Baron to name the beautiful <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Eriostemon</hi>
               </seg> after the Hon: J.H. Carruthers, Minister for Public Instruction, who has been a good friend to the Museum, &amp; has done much to further technical education in N.S.W. To call it after the other gentleman would have no appropriateness, and would not be understood. […]</p>
         </div>
